THE usual battle order of the legion-soldiers was a threefold line (acies triplex) made by arranging the maniples in three rows or ranks. Between the maniples of each row there was lest space about equal in width to the face of the maniple 3 and the maniples of each row stood opposite the vacant spaces of the other row nearest to it, like the squares on a checker-board (see pl.
